---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Updated Alimony Rules · Pro Se Fair Play Mediation"
  description="Florida's alimony laws changed on July 1, 2023. Permanent alimony is no longer available; courts now focus on shorter-term support designed to help a spouse become financially independent."
>
  <!-- ========================== HEADER ========================== -->
  <header class="article-header">
    <div class="container article-header-inner">
      <p class="kicker reveal reveal-d1">
        <span class="kicker-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span>
        Florida Family Law
      </p>
      <h1 class="display article-title reveal reveal-d2">
        Updated <span class="title-keep"><span class="display-italic">Alimony</span> Rules<span class="display-italic">.</span></span>
      </h1>
      <p class="lede reveal reveal-d3">
        Florida's alimony laws changed on July 1, 2023. One of the biggest
        changes is that permanent alimony is no longer available. Instead,
        courts now focus on shorter-term forms of financial support designed to
        help a spouse become financially independent.
      </p>
    </div>
  </header>

  <!-- ========================== BODY ========================== -->
  <section class="article-body">
    <div class="container-narrow article-prose">
      <h2>Types of Alimony in Florida</h2>

      <h3>Bridge-the-Gap Alimony</h3>
      <p>
        This is short-term support that helps a spouse adjust to life after
        divorce. It can last up to two years.
      </p>

      <h3>Rehabilitative Alimony</h3>
      <p>
        This type of alimony helps a spouse gain the education, training, or
        skills needed to return to work. It requires a specific rehabilitation
        plan approved by the court.
      </p>

      <h3>Durational Alimony</h3>
      <p>
        Durational alimony provides financial support for a limited period of
        time. The maximum length depends on how long the marriage lasted:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Less than 3 years: Generally not available.</li>
        <li>3 to 10 years (Short-Term Marriage): Up to 50% of the length of the marriage.</li>
        <li>10 to 20 years (Moderate-Term Marriage): Up to 60% of the length of the marriage.</li>
        <li>20 years or more (Long-Term Marriage): Up to 75% of the length of the marriage.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        The length of the marriage is calculated from the date of marriage to
        the date the divorce petition is filed.
      </p>

      <h2>How Is the Amount Determined?</h2>
      <p>The court generally awards the lower of:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>The receiving spouse's reasonable financial need, or</li>
        <li>35% of the difference between the spouses' net incomes (after taxes).</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        The court also considers many other factors, including each spouse's
        income, earning ability, health, age, contributions during the
        marriage, and overall financial circumstances.
      </p>

      <h2>The Advantage of Mediation</h2>
      <p>
        When a judge decides your case, the court must follow Florida law.
        During mediation, however, you and your spouse have the opportunity to
        create your own agreement. As long as both parties voluntarily agree,
        mediation often provides more flexibility and allows families to reach
        practical solutions tailored to their unique needs.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ========================== CLOSING CTA ========================== -->
  <section class="article-cta">
    <div class="container-narrow article-cta-inner">
      <a class="btn btn-primary article-cta-btn" href="/book">
        Book a Free, Private Consultation
        <span class="arrow" aria-hidden="true">→</span>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  /* ============================================================
     HEADER — cream, mirrors the legal pages
     ============================================================ */
  .article-header {
    position: relative;
    padding-block: clamp(4rem, 6vw + 1rem, 6rem) clamp(2rem, 3vw, 3rem);
    background:
      radial-gradient(ellipse at 80% 20%, rgba(196, 154, 75, 0.08), transparent 55%),
      var(--color-cream);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-divider);
    overflow: hidden;
  }
  .article-header-inner { position: relative; max-width: 64rem; }
  .article-title {
    margin-top: 1rem;
    font-size: var(--step-5);
    line-height: 1.04;
    color: var(--color-navy);
    letter-spacing: -0.025em;
    max-width: 20ch;
    font-weight: 400;
    text-wrap: balance;
  }
  .article-title .display-italic { color: var(--color-gold-deep); font-weight: 400; }
  /* Keep "Alimony Rules." together so it drops as one block
     ("Updated" / "Alimony Rules.") on desktop. */
  .article-title .title-keep { white-space: nowrap; }
  .article-header .lede {
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
    max-width: 62ch;
    color: var(--color-ink-soft);
  }

  /* ============================================================
     BODY PROSE
     ============================================================ */
  .article-body {
    padding-block: var(--space-lg) var(--space-3xl);
    background: var(--color-cream);
  }
  .article-prose {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: var(--step-1);
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-ink-soft);
  }
  .article-prose p { max-width: 64ch; }
  .article-prose p + p,
  .article-prose ul + p { margin-top: 1.25rem; }
  .article-prose h2 {
    margin-top: var(--space-xl);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    padding-top: 1.25rem;
    border-top: 2px solid var(--color-gold);
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: var(--step-3);
    line-height: 1.1;
    color: var(--color-navy);
    letter-spacing: -0.015em;
    font-weight: 400;
  }
  .article-prose h2:first-child {
    margin-top: 0;
    padding-top: 0;
    border-top: none;
  }
  .article-prose h3 {
    margin-top: 1.75rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-variation-settings: "opsz" 24;
    font-size: 1.3rem;
    line-height: 1.25;
    color: var(--color-navy);
    letter-spacing: -0.005em;
    font-weight: 500;
  }
  .article-prose ul {
    margin: 1rem 0 1.25rem;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.45rem;
    max-width: 64ch;
  }
  .article-prose li { line-height: 1.55; }
  .article-prose strong { color: var(--color-navy); font-weight: 600; }

  /* ============================================================
     CLOSING CTA — button only
     ============================================================ */
  .article-cta {
    position: relative;
    padding-block: var(--space-lg);
    background: var(--color-cream-warm);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-divider);
  }
  .article-cta::before {
    content: "";
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0 0 auto 0;
    height: 1px;
    background: linear-gradient(90deg, transparent, var(--color-gold) 40%, var(--color-gold) 60%, transparent);
    opacity: 0.7;
  }
  .article-cta-inner { display: flex; justify-content: center; }
  .article-cta-btn {
    background: var(--color-navy);
    color: var(--color-cream);
    border-color: var(--color-navy);
  }
  .article-cta-btn:hover {
    background: var(--color-navy-deep);
    color: var(--color-cream);
    border-color: var(--color-gold);
  }

  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .article-title { font-size: clamp(2.25rem, 1.8rem + 3vw, 3.5rem); }
    /* On phones, let the title wrap freely (balanced) instead of forcing
       the desktop one-block break. */
    .article-title .title-keep { white-space: normal; }
  }
</style>
